# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# Example: feat(auth): add login functionality
#
# Types:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation changes)
#   style    (formatting, missing semicolons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   test     (adding missing tests, refactoring tests)
#   chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
#
# Scope:
#   auth     (authentication related changes)
#   store    (state management changes)
#   ui       (user interface components)
#   api      (API integration changes)
#   test     (test infrastructure changes)
#   deps     (dependency updates)
#   ci       (CI configuration changes)
#   *        (multiple scopes or scope-less)
#
# Subject: (max 50 chars)
#   - Use imperative mood ("Add" not "Added" or "Adds")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period (.) at the end
#
# Body: (optional, wrap at 72 chars)
# Explain the motivation for the change and contrast it with previous behavior
#
# Footer: (optional)
# Include references to issues and breaking changes
# Example: Closes #123, BREAKING CHANGE: auth API endpoints changed
#
